The paper proposes a Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) based framework for content caching in next-generation wireless networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of DRL. The paper also involves optimization and decision-making, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with control problems, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves information theory and communication networks, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
